  "prompt": "How do I delete my gmail only from one device and retain the same on other devices?",
  "response": "The process depends on the device you want to remove your Gmail account from. Here's a breakdown for the most common devices:\n\n**1. Android Phone or Tablet:**\n\n*   **Using the Gmail App:**\n    1.  Open the Gmail app.\n    2.  Tap your profile picture (top right).\n    3.  Tap \"Manage accounts on this device\".\n    4.  Tap the Google account (Gmail account) you want to remove.\n    5.  Tap \"Remove account\".  (On some older versions of Android, it might say \"Sign out\").\n    6.  Confirm the removal if prompted.\n\n*   **Using the System Settings:**\n    1.  Open your device's \"Settings\" app.\n    2.  Search for \"Accounts\" or \"Users & accounts\" (the exact wording varies by Android version).\n    3.  Tap \"Accounts\".\n    4.  Tap the Google account (Gmail account) you want to remove.\n    5.  Tap \"Remove account\".\n    6.  Confirm the removal.\n\n**Important Notes for Android:**\n\n*   Removing the Google account from your Android device will also remove access to other Google services associated with that account (like Google Play, Google Drive, etc.) on *that specific device*.  Your data will still be available on other devices where you're logged in.\n*   Some Android devices require a Google account to function fully. Removing the only account might limit some features.\n\n**2. iPhone or iPad (iOS):**\n\n*   **Using the Gmail App:**\n    1.  Open the Gmail app.\n    2.  Tap the menu icon (three horizontal lines, usually in the top left).\n    3.  Tap your account name/email at the top.\n    4.  Tap \"Manage accounts\".\n    5.  Tap \"Edit\" (top right).\n    6.  Tap the red minus sign \"-\" next to the account you want to remove.\n    7.  Tap \"Delete\".\n    8.  Tap \"Done\".\n\n*   **Using the iOS Settings:**\n    1.  Open the \"Settings\" app.\n    2.  Scroll down and tap \"Mail\" (or \"Contacts\" or \"Calendar\" if your Gmail account is used for those services).\n    3.  Tap \"Accounts\".\n    4.  Tap the Gmail account you want to remove.\n    5.  Tap \"Delete Account\".\n    6.  Confirm the deletion.\n\n**3. Computer (Web Browser - Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge, etc.):**\n\n*   **You're not actually deleting the *account* from the device.** You're simply signing out of the Gmail website.\n    1.  Open Gmail in your web browser (mail.google.com).\n    2.  Click your profile picture (top right).\n    3.  Click \"Sign out\" or \"Sign out of all accounts\".  If you only want to sign out of *one* specific Gmail account and you have multiple signed in, choose the \"Sign out\" option for *that* specific account.\n\n**Important Considerations and Troubleshooting:**\n\n*   **Password:**  You'll need your Google account password to remove the account from most devices.\n*   **2-Step Verification:** If you have 2-Step Verification (2FA) enabled, you might need to use a verification code from your authenticator app, SMS, or backup codes to confirm the removal.\n*   **Account Sync:**  After removing the account, make sure that syncing for that account is turned off on the device you removed it from.  This prevents the device from trying to re-add the account automatically.\n*   **Browser Cookies and Cache:**  Clearing your browser's cookies and cache can sometimes help if you're having trouble signing out of Gmail on a computer.\n*   **Device-Specific Instructions:**  If you're using a less common device or operating system, consult the manufacturer's instructions for removing accounts.\n\nBy following these steps, you can remove your Gmail account from a specific device while keeping it active on your other devices. Remember to double-check that you're removing the account from the correct device and that you have your password handy.\n",
